   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF FIRST AND SECOND SAMUEL MESSAGE THIRTY-FIVE THE HISTORY CONCERNING DAVID 13 CROWNED BY THE PEOPLE TO BE THE KING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>FOR THE KINGDOM OF GOD ON THE EARTH</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>2 SAMUEL 2 24 7 GOD'S PUNISHING JUDGMENT ON DAVID</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>2 SAMUEL 12:15b 20:26 1 Scripture Reading: 2 Sam 12:15b 14:33</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Second Samuel 12:15b through 14:33 describes God's punishing judgment on David.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>I. THE DEATH OF THE CHILD BORN OF URIAH'S WIFE</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In 12:15b-23 we are told of the death of the child born to David of Uriah's wife.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>A. Jehovah Striking the Child with Heavy Sickness</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Jehovah struck the child whom Uriah's wife bore to David, and the child was very sick v. 15b .</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>B. David Beseeching God for the Child</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>David besought God for the child with fasting, spending all the night lying on the ground v. 16 .</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>C. The Child Dying and David Being Released</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>On the seventh day the child died and David was released vv.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>17-23 .</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>When David realized that the child had died, he rose up from the ground, washed and anointed himself, changed his clothes, and went into the house of Jehovah and worshipped.</S>
   </TEXT>
